data.chText: 男爵（最低一级贵族。英国男爵头衔为Lord；其他国家为Baron）
data.enText: a nobleman of the lowest rank. In Britain, barons use the title Lord ; in other countries they use the title Baron .
a person who owns or controls a large part of a particular industry

word_means: 男爵(最低一级贵族。英国男爵头衔为Lord
simple_means.memory_skill: 来自拉丁文baro，意为男人 + on 人 → 大财主

means: 男爵(最低一级贵族。英国男爵头衔为Lord

tr: a very wealthy or powerful businessman
a British peer of the lowest rank
a nobleman (in various countries) of varying rank

value.def: A baron is a man who is a member of the lowest rank of the nobility.

example.tran: 他们的继父，迈克尔·迪斯腾普尔男爵

value.tran: 男爵（贵族爵位中最低的一级）

value.def: You can use baron to refer to someone who controls a large amount of a particular industry or activity and who is therefore extremely powerful.

trans: 强盗贵族，强盗资本家(指用非法或不道德手段攫取大量钱财的权贵)
